Que 1.  List 3 real-world scenarios where your favorite apps (like Zomato, WhatsApp, or Spotify) use local storage to improve user experience when there is no internet connection, and explain in 1-2 lines how local storage helps in each case.

Ans :-

1. WhatsApp

WhatsApp stores chats, photos, videos, and documents locally on the user's device. 
This allows users to read previous conversations and view downloaded media even when there is no internet connection. 
Once the internet is available again, new messages are synchronized automatically.

2. Spotify

Spotify saves downloaded songs, playlists, and albums in local storage. 
This enables users to listen to their favorite music offline without using mobile data or an internet connection.
The app also remembers the user's playlists and listening history for a smooth experience.

3. Zomato

Zomato caches recently viewed restaurants, menus, and search results in local storage. 
If the internet connection is lost, users can still view recently opened restaurant information, menu details, and saved favorites. 
This helps users quickly access important information even when they are offline.
